4w.title: Inductive ambiguity identification and querying
4w.clickbait: What's the one common property of a "red strawberry", a "red apple", and a "red cherry"?
4w.text: An open problem in value alignment.  Given a labeled data set, try to identify ambiguities in which inductive concepts could cover the data, and query the user about those ambiguities.  E.g., suppose you are given images that show enemy tanks and empty forests, and it so happens that all the tank pictures were taken on cloudy days, and all empty forest pictures were taken on sunny days.  A hypothetical algorithm that notices this and asks "Hey, did you mean to point to tanks, cloudiness, either, or both?", rather than only learning the luminosity dimension or a combined luminosity-and-tankness dimension, is doing "inductive ambiguity identification and querying".
